OL,3,C'One in three kids' missing out on
OL,4,Cschool trips due to cost
OL,6,FThe trips are designed to complement
OL,7,Ftheir learning throughout the year.
OL,8,FThey've learnt about conflict, so
OL,9,Fthey're visiting the Imperial War
OL,10,FMuseum. They've learnt different
OL,11,Fperformances, so they're visiting a
OL,12,Ftheatre.
OL,14,FThe trips are planned really well to
OL,15,Fenhance their curriculum and we've got
OL,16,Fchildren who sadly have to miss out."
OL,18,FPepe Di'Lasio, General Secretary of
OL,19,Fthe Association of School and College
OL,20,FLeaders says the rising costs are due
OL,21,Fto a number of factors:
